author: COMSOL
description: This example models a thin oil reservoir with two horizontal wells. The reservoir contains two phases, water and oil. The oil is recovered by injecting water through the bottom well. The model is used to compute the oil production rate and the water-oil production ratio over time.
label: reservoir_horizontal_wells.mph
name: root
